===Etymology===
[L. intimatio: cf. F. intimation.]

===Noun===
#The act of intimating; also, the thing intimated.
#Announcement; declaration.
#:'''Qutations'''
#:*They made an edict with an ''intimation'' that whosoever killed a stork, should be banished. &mdash; Holland.
#A hint; an obscure or indirect suggestion or notice; a remote or ambiguous reference; as, he had given only intimations of his design.
#:'''Qutations'''
#:*Without mentioning the king of England, or giving the least intimation that he was sent by him. &mdash; Bp. Burnet.
#:*At length, perchance, the immaterial heaven will appear as much higher to the American mind, and the ''intimations'' that star it as much brighter. &mdash; 1862 [[w:Henry David Thoreau|Thoreau]], [http://wikisource.org/wiki/Walking ''Walking''].